review_blob: By no means an outstanding beer but none the less drinkable. Distinctive amber appearance with a strong, long lasting finish. Its a struggle to drink in large amounts tho due to the strength of the beer. But for what it is and the price it sells at its great.
Im drinking on at this very moment! lively carbonation with a long finish. Amber/copper colour with a mild roasted flavour.
A creamy off-white head with a distinctive coffee aroma. A favourtie dark drop of mine.
